{
  "texts": [
    "PromptComposition.",
    "The quality of a generated test is directly determined by the completeness of the information provided in the prompt.",
    "Each component of the prompt is designed to address a specific challenge in the unit test generation process, as detailed in Table 2.Basic and Enhanced Static Context.",
    "While source code serves as the foundational context, relying solely on it often leads to compilation errors caused by missing dependencies.",
    "To address this, recent studies widely employ static analysis techniques to extract class constructors, method signatures, and key dependency information [27,118], aiming to construct a semantically complete context."
  ]
}